The '''''Skyriver Invader''''' was a [[Starship/Legends|starship]] used by the [[Zeta Magnus (clone)|genetic decoy]] of [[Zeta Magnus]] during his stint as [[Magister of Skye|Magister]] of [[Skye/Legends|Skye]] in [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]]. A strange, triangular craft, it reminded the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] [[Halagad Ventor]] of a T-11 model he used to play with as a [[Youngling/Legends|youngling]]. [[Zeta Magnus]] named the ship after the [[The galaxy/Legends|main galaxy]] used by the [[Nagai/Legends|Nagai]], an [[Firefist|extragalactic]] [[Species/Legends|species]] who he encountered in the [[Unknown Regions/Legends|Unknown Regions]] and acquired [[Cloaking device/Legends|cloaking technology]] from. The [[Cloning/Legends|clone]] of Zeta Magnus held his ship in the [[Hangar/Legends|hangar bay]] of his [[Canaitith Mountain|mountaintop]] [[Kharys' fortress|fortress]] on the planet Skye. When Magnus tried to escape the planet after a group of three Jedi foiled his plans, [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] Ventor stopped the [[mutant]] by impaling him with a [[Liquid-cable launcher/Legends|liquid cable spike]]. While the mutant attempted to eat the padawan, he was betrayed by his [[Droid/Legends|droid]] [[Blue-Tark/Legends|Blue-Tark]] who ignited the ship's thrusters and blasted off. The [[Zeta Magnus (clone)|Zeta Magnus]] clone was slain by Ventor after he was burned and irradiated by his ship's [[Ion engine/Legends|ion drive]].<ref name="SkyeWalkers">''[[SkyeWalkers: A Clone Wars Story]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
[[File:Apex_Invader_concept_BW.jpg|thumb|right|250px|''Apex Invader'' concept art]]
The ''Skyriver Invader'' was based on a proposed but never produced vehicle for the rejected extension of [[Kenner Products|Kenner's]] ''[[Star Wars]]'' toy line, ''[[The Epic Continues]]'', known as the ''Apex Invader''. According to the craft's fictional story, ''Apex Invader'' was new villain [[Atha Prime/Legends|Atha Prime's]] personal [[Starfighter/Legends|starfighter]]. The craft was able to attach atop Prime's [[Starship/Legends|starship]], [[Annihilator (starship)|''Annihilator'']], which gave him the ultimate command vantage point for battles. It was used as his personal fighting vehicle and was piloted by his [[Pilot/Legends|pilot]] [[Droid/Legends|droid]] [[Blue-Tark/Legends|Blue-Four]].<ref name="Tales">{{GalaxyCite|2|Galactic Bazaar|Galactic Bazaar: Tales of Phantom Toys}}</ref>

